This is the website of the Collaborative IVENA statistics project. We provide statistics about german emergency medicine with the help of IVENA, which is a tool that is used to dispatch patients to hospitals.
For full access to this project, you need to login. If you don't already have a login you can register yourself.

We currently have %allocations% allocations from %hospitals% hospitals in our database. We're constantly adding more and more statistics generated from this database. And the best: Some of your statistics are available for free without login!
We are currently waiting for your verification process to be completed before you can get started. In the meantime you can take a look at our statistics of the FAQ.

This export includes the monthly counts of several indication codes during the years 2019 to 2021. These codes are 124, 130, 310, 311, 312, 315, 326, 331, 332, 333, 348, 349, 354, 376, 377, 421, 422, 423, 511, 512, 513 and the respective counts are listed by urgencies ranging from SK1 (highest urgency) to SK3 (lowest urgency).
